                        Rev. 3, 16. if we doe not as one man humble our ſelues, for partaking with Idols, and ſuffering of Idols, and every man in his place put to his hand, to bring Iezabel from the window; we may juſtly feare, that neither peace, nor warre, nor Parliament, nor Plantation, nor Traffique ſhall proſper with us? Yea, to ſhut up the point; if we will neither hearken to counſell nor threatning, we may feare, that be made good upon us which the Prophet threatned againſt Amaziah; that God hath determined to destroy us;
2 Chr. 25.1
